OL,3,CBerkshire breakfast club is 'a
OL,4,Clifeline'
OL,6,FEvery second Saturday of the month,
OL,7,Fthe Salvation Army Hall opens its
OL,8,Fdoors, puts the kettle on and prepares
OL,9,Fa slap-up breakfast. However, it is
OL,10,Fless about the food and more about
OL,11,Fconnections and friendship. Its
OL,12,Ffounder Keith Vertigan explains: "I
OL,13,Fdid 25 years as a regular soldier, 9
OL,14,Fyears as a reservist and I'm a fitness
OL,15,Finstructor, so, having a brain
OL,16,Fhaemorrhage just put me on standstill.
OL,17,FI had three months off where I wasn't
OL,18,Fallowed to work and I really suffered.
OL,19,FI then did talking therapies, I did an
OL,20,Fon-line mental health first aid course
OL,21,Fand it was just from there really. We
OL,22,Fput our heads together and thought,
OL,23,Flet's do a men's breakfast."
